1
00:00:03,080 --> 00:00:10,314
Our taking of Kṛṣṇa-nam
is a service aspiration,

2
00:00:10,314 --> 00:00:19,703
not to free ourselves
of impending karmic reactions.

3
00:00:20,258 --> 00:00:22,931
[Guns, God, and Goodness]

4
00:00:23,946 --> 00:00:30,051
Like Flannery O’Connor, a famous writer, 
southern writer of short stories,

5
00:00:30,051 --> 00:00:36,484
she has a famous short story called 
A Good Man is Hard to Find,

6
00:00:36,484 --> 00:00:40,723
and without going into 
the details of the story …

7
00:00:40,723 --> 00:00:44,739
some family who's out for an outing,
their car brakes down, blah blah blah …

8
00:00:44,739 --> 00:00:49,657
long story short: in the end there's
a man who's trying to kill them all,

9
00:00:49,657 --> 00:00:52,033
and when he points the gun
to this one woman,

10
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:55,822
at that point she becomes 
very religious

11
00:00:55,822 --> 00:01:01,498
—this is sort of like
the key part of the story—

12
00:01:01,498 --> 00:01:07,996
and she makes this sort of, you could say,
cynical, or s[notty]... an observation, she's saying …

13
00:01:07,996 --> 00:01:10,914
Gee, I mean,
she would have been very fortunate

14
00:01:10,914 --> 00:01:13,832
if at every moment in her life

15
00:01:13,832 --> 00:01:16,752
someone had a gun
pointed to her head.

16
00:01:16,752 --> 00:01:20,912
Then she would have 
really been holy.

17
00:01:24,190 --> 00:01:31,831
So, the devotees are not taking
Kṛṣṇa-nam or aproaching Kṛṣṇa

18
00:01:31,831 --> 00:01:35,934
to escape impending
karmic reactions,

19
00:01:35,934 --> 00:01:41,180
but rather
offering themselves in service

20
00:01:41,180 --> 00:01:46,099
to the lotus feet of 
Guru and Gauranga, Rādhā-Govinda,

21
00:01:47,115 --> 00:01:50,277
and whatever service will come
through that line to them,

22
00:01:50,277 --> 00:01:57,157
they’re very honored, privileged, 
happy to accept that.

23
00:01:57,664 --> 00:02:01,650
Guru Mahārāj made the point, 
he said that in the spiritual world—

24
00:02:01,650 --> 00:02:03,517
you can see in posters

25
00:02:03,517 --> 00:02:09,183
or you won’t see in posters—
gopīs chanting on the japa-mala.

26
00:02:10,060 --> 00:02:13,572
You don’t hear … some Vraja-gopīs,
they go, “We need, you know

27
00:02:13,572 --> 00:02:18,071
it’s time to churn the butter, 
make yoghurt”,

28
00:02:18,071 --> 00:02:21,525
[and another gopī replies],
“No, I've got to chant my rounds.”

29
00:02:21,525 --> 00:02:24,629
[laughs]

30
00:02:24,629 --> 00:02:29,575
No, we’re told, when 
they’re churning, their bangles

31
00:02:29,944 --> 00:02:33,396
are making some sound, 
and they're singing

32
00:02:33,446 --> 00:02:36,499
about the pastimes of Kṛṣṇa.

33
00:02:36,499 --> 00:02:40,594
Viśvanāth Chakravartī Ṭhākur
and others like to point out,

34
00:02:40,594 --> 00:02:43,321
when some events 
happen in Vṛndāvan,

35
00:02:43,321 --> 00:02:51,565
these Vraja-gopīs, they’re very 
capable poets, singers, composers—

36
00:02:51,565 --> 00:02:55,545
they start composing songs 
spontaneously

37
00:02:55,545 --> 00:02:59,454
about the pastimes of Kṛṣṇa,
while they’re doing their different sevā.

38
00:02:59,454 --> 00:03:04,969
Vande Nanda-vraja-strīṇāḿ
pāda-reṇum abhīkṣṇaśaḥ

39
00:03:04,969 --> 00:03:12,240
yāsāḿ Hari-kathodgītaḿ
punāti bhuvana-trayam 
[SB: 10.47.63].

40
00:03:12,024 --> 00:03:18,310
And this vibration that’s coming from them
is purifing everywhere,

41
00:03:18,310 --> 00:03:21,515
and they’re just churning butter, 
making different things,

42
00:03:21,515 --> 00:03:25,632
going about 
their household duties,

43
00:03:25,632 --> 00:03:32,563
because at that point, Śrīla Guru Mahārāj
said, “Kṛṣṇa-nam is automatic,

44
00:03:32,563 --> 00:03:37,753
they’re situated in Kṛṣṇa-nam.”

45
00:03:37,753 --> 00:03:40,898
Kṛṣṇa-mantra haite habe saṁsāra-mocana

46
00:03:40,898 --> 00:03:44,904
Kṛṣṇa-nāma haite pābe Kṛṣṇera caraṇa
[Cc: 1.7.73].

47
00:03:44,904 --> 00:03:50,514
The mantram, a mantra with Kṛṣṇa in it,
will liberate one (saṁsāra-mocana);

48
00:03:50,637 --> 00:03:55,087
but Kṛṣṇa-nam
—a contrast is being drawn here:

49
00:03:55,087 --> 00:03:59,625
Kṛṣṇa-nam will take one to the service 
of the lotus feet of Kṛṣṇa,

50
00:03:59,625 --> 00:04:05,564
and when one has achieved that,
it’s on automatic.

51
00:04:09,067 --> 00:04:10,498
Hare Kṛṣṇa.

